Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%oz} lengthwise. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%oz} into 1-inch pieces.

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}.

Meanwhile, mash potatoes with @sour cream{4%tbsp} and @butter{2%tbsp} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

> Use 3 TBSP butter instead of 2 for 4 servings.

Heat pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, @fig jam{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide mashed potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and chicken between plates. Drizzle chicken with sauce and serve.